The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Metro | Six injured in three mishaps
                                                                                                               Six injured in three mishaps
          A STAFF REPORTER                              
	Six people were injured in three road accidents in Howrah on Tuesday. The injured were admitted to the district hospital.         
	Three persons, including a 71-year-old man, were injured when the Ambassador they were travelling in rammed into a truck near Batore More, on Kona Expressway, around 11.40am.        
	Police said the driver of the car lost control after the brakes failed.        
	Residents took Bhabani Banerjee, his 53-year-old daughter Bandana Sen and their driver to the district hospital. The duo were returning home to Uttarpara, in Hooghly, after meeting a doctor in Ballygunge. The condition of all three was stated to be critical.        
	Around noon, two persons riding a motorcycle were injured after being hit by a taxi on National Highway 6, near Chamrail.        
	Members of a national highway rescue team took Supriya Sarkar, 28, and Debjit Chandra, 29, to the district hospital.        
	Sarkar is a resident of Kali Kundu Lane, and Chandra, of Sadar Baksi Lane. The police said the driver of the taxi fled with the vehicle.        
	The national highway team also rescued a 25-year-old motorcyclist who was lying unconscious near a bridge in Bally in the morning. The two-wheeler was lying a few feet away.         
	The police suspect the youth, identified as Shib Chandra Mahato, was injured after a vehicle hit the motorcycle. Mahato was later admitted to the district hospital. His condition was stated to be critical.                                                                                                                                                                           
